    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="894"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d894">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Takahira</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Japanese Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Information having reached Japan of the appalling
                    extent of the misfortune which has overtaken the people of Galveston, His <pb
                        facs="0866" n="768" xml:id="pg_768"/> Imperial Majesty’s minister for
                    foreign affairs has directed me by telegraph to assure the Government of the
                    United States of the profound sympathy of the Imperial Government with those who
                    suffered directly by this terrible calamity, as well as with those indirectly
                    affected by its wide-reaching results, and to tender to them the sincere
                    condolence of the Government and people of Japan.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">K. Takahira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
